# Deploy after changes

When you finish edits that affect the live app or backend config, run deployment from the project root **in the same turn** (unless the user explicitly says not to deploy):

```bash
firebase deploy
```

Applies when touching any of: `public/**`, `firebase.json`, `firestore.rules`, `firestore.indexes.json`, `storage.rules`, `.firebaserc`.

Do **not** deploy for documentation-only or `.md`-only changes unless the user asks.

If `firebase` fails (not installed, not logged in), report the error and what the user should run locally.
